#: ../../validation.rst:3
msgid "Validation Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:5
msgid "Validation is the process of assessing a file using the `IATI Standard <https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/>`_. Both the schema and the rulesets are used in validation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:7
msgid "Both Activity and Organisation files can be validated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:9
msgid "Validation only covers areas of the standard that can be checked by a computer: some requirements of the IATI standard (such as that text is descriptive) are subjective and therefore are not included in validation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:11
msgid "Validation only checks the structure of the data: no attempt is made to verify that the data is true or accurate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:13
msgid "The result of this process is a report, which shows the :ref:`status<Statuses>` of the file, and details of any issues found. Issues are grouped into :ref:`categories<Categories>` for ease of comprehension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../validation.rst:15
msgid "When an Activity file is validated, the whole file is assessed and given a status. As long as the file doesn't have Critical status, each individual activity is then assessed and assigned a status. The file's status will always be that of the most serious single issue discovered in the file."
msgstr ""
